      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "JUST A DUKE (3) flew the lids with a slick early split last time and went on to clock 27.86 as a strongly fancied winner over 488m at this track. Ran one of the fastest times on the program in his latest win. Has hit winning form and can measure up again. ASH ROSE (2) missed the frame latest when sixth at this track (23.75) but scored three back at this track (17.21). Solid record here at the distance winning two races. Likely to play a prominent role. BOILER MAKER (1) was responsible for a modest effort most recently when fifth at this track over 400m behind Blue And Boujee (23.02) in a Grade 5. Remains without a win from the draw but has been in the placings three times from six attempts. Key player if finds best. SUNSET VANADIUM (4) was in the money again last time and not beaten far when second (22.87) at this track in a Grade 5.",
